_:N98ec28f593a248fd99e90b47a3cdebe7 <http://schema.org/description> "The Royal Air Force Museum (RAFM) tells the story of British aviation, from early bi-planes to the latest strike-jets. It is based on two sites - Colindale in North London, and Cosford in Shropshire, and is free to visit. RAFM is an executive non-departmental public body, sponsored by the Ministry of Defence ." .
<https://www.gov.uk/> <http://schema.org/name> "Home" .
